{"success": true, "message": "Fetched question.", "data": {"showTimer": true, "showAttemptInsight": true, "playSounds": true, "dontShowCorrectAnswerImmediately": false, "_id": "648b5a6f417cc3fb48d68062", "classes": [], "exams": ["615d76b2c52ffa3c944600df"], "subjects": ["615d708dbd4a37c4058ee5a8"], "chapters": ["615d6fed2b295b085ab6eba1"], "topics": [], "concepts": [], "previousYearPapers": [{"_id": "63f499841d196b49d9cd6b0b", "title": "JEE Main 2023 (25 Jan Shift 1)", "isVisible": true}], "position": 0, "type": "singleCorrect", "level": 1, "approximateTimeRequired": 90, "question": {"text": "All electromagnetic wave is transporting energy in the negative <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>z</mi></math> direction. At a certain point and certain time the direction of electric field of the wave is along positive <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi></math> direction. What will be the direction of the magnetic field of the wave at that point and instant?", "image": null}, "options": [{"id": "0c71a", "text": "Positive direction of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>", "isCorrect": true, "image": null}, {"id": "Hj95b", "text": "Positive direction of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>z</mi></math>", "isCorrect": false, "image": null}, {"id": "ALSiK", "text": "Negative direction of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>", "isCorrect": false, "image": null}, {"id": "Kq7c8", "text": "Negative direction of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi></math>", "isCorrect": false, "image": null}], "correctValue": null, "solution": {"text": "<p>In an electromagnetic wave, the direction of energy flow is along the direction of the wave propagation. Therefore, the wave propagates along negative z direction.&nbsp;</p><p>Electric field is along the positive y direction and the wave propagates along negative z direction. Thus, magnetic&nbsp;field is in&nbsp;direction perpendicular to both z&nbsp;and y axes.&nbsp;</p><p>Using vector algebra,&nbsp;</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mo>-</mo><mover><mi>k</mi><mo mathvariant=\"italic\">^</mo></mover><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>(</mo><mo>+</mo><mover><mi>j</mi><mo mathvariant=\"italic\">^</mo></mover><mo>)</mo><mo>&#215;</mo><mfenced><mover><mi>i</mi><mo>^</mo></mover></mfenced></math></p><p>Hence,&nbsp;magnetic field is in positive <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math> direction.</p>", "image": null}, "videoSolution": null, "numericalUpperLimit": null, "numericalLowerLimit": null, "questionLabels": [], "__v": 0, "masterId": "MOGJMPYQ41002349", "bucket": "Easy Ques (Board Level)", "category": null, "microConcepts": [], "imageBaseUrl": null, "helperText": null, "isRemoved": false, "cpyqbSubjects": ["61bb58181213731910ea0b70", "61c055eae8ce0dc8a5c62d33", "616057750283de43c87e3e1b", "61964fe0a5a5260118868021", "61964f81a5a526011886801d", "629f39e4ac11b26562e0625b", "616057920283de43c87e3e1e", "615f0c729476412f48314dab", "61a8a2c2e8ce0dc8a5c62d2d", "629105adee9e3ae00d63352b", "629f385f263330a77be9fa7d", "616056cd0283de43c87e3e15", "616057190283de43c87e3e18", "62962075e7f8e9ac4daeafd7", "64d50bd73df7f4a7f3017f6f", "66b79b34d4b564dfab4f94cc", "678ea9a09cc79e5f592bdc11", "67fa5fef4468eb1307ceb0ad", "6807d2ad647479b8e8696479"], "cpyqbChapters": ["622892fd9f7523577cddc56f", "616024349a1ab852c3621f3c", "61602434741e389e3bfe9c28", "61964c90dbd361e84674fcb5", "61602435374ba1acd615152b", "61bb82195b64558bcac5c98d", "61602433079526ff68bf2908", "61964c91fa250eeb00025cd9", "61c0899871fb803161367f9f", "61e7bd75cfe22022f28241f6", "629109eb647e2f0fcf939346", "62962122b0ae2c997a812c36", "629f390b3ea045f798a076c3", "629f3a904e5aa634f7fe6aca", "64eb06c43118f713ecfef0a5", "66d58538a75f05ee8564f558", "67921d6c1d5b5072da5e9af1", "67fdff4f378e1624ea7b69fa", "680920353a10446a207fdf58"], "cpyqbExams": ["615f0e999476412f48314